GM! I'm TPan and I write about various Web3 topics 5x/week at tpan.substack.com. 

I'm going to share my daily 'pre-writing' notes here, feel free to chime in. 

So many thoughts, topics, and questions, so why not have you all join in on the fun and have a peek into my brain! 🙂
Shoutout to  for onboarding me! I was a little intimidated at first ngl, but Farcaster is dope.

To kick off my first 'pre-writing' Cast, tomorrow will be my 100th piece. 

I started writing about NFT/Web3 topics on April 7th. 

I write about 1-2k words a day. I'm going to count how many words I've written later tonight lol.

It's going to be more of a personal post vs. a Web3 one. 

It'll be nice to share an update on my journey from Growth/Marketing professional in Web2 tech --> taking a hard right into Web3 and exploring writing --> ???

As for where I'm going to take my writing, I believe there are 3 PMF hypotheses I want to test for the rest of the year:

- Conferences
- Web3 Companies
- VC Funds

All 3 create content across multiple mediums, but generally lack a couple things:

- Great written content
- Personality

Nothing wrong with that, just my opinion.

I think I can provide that, and will be reaching out to companies in those three categories to see if there are opportunities out there.

Memes. 

How do memes in Web1, Web2, and Web3 compare, and why they will continue to take over the world.

https://tpan.substack.com/p/dive-106-memes

Nuggets pt. 1

- Term coined by British evolutionary biologist in 1976
- 'Meme' comes from the Greek word mimema, 'imitated'
- Cultural parallel to biological genes, specifically selfish genes

Nuggets pt. 2

If memes viewed as selfish genes:

- Memes carry information, are replicated, and are transmitted from one person to another
- They have the ability to evolve, mutating at random and undergoing natural selection
- Genetics = study of genes Memetics = study of memes

Nuggets pt. 3

Web1 Memes: Access to memes limited, access to distributing memes limited

- America's Funniest Home Videos
- Budweiser 'WASSSUP' ad
- Comic strips in newspapers

Whoops, turning into a thread 😂

Web2 Memes: Mass access to memes, Mass access to distributing memes

- Due to social media platforms!
- For a cause (eg: ALS ice bucket challenge)
- Celebrities (Celebrities read mean tweets about themselves)
- Brands (fast food chain meme game)

Memes are interoperable

- With the visual context/setting, you understand the meme and joke. 
- Even if you don’t understand the content within the meme, you have a directional understanding. https://i.imgur.com/ULFDlkU.png
